post_text:
At Manhattan Charter School, we always try to get involved in the community and cultivate a sense of compassion among our students. Recently, under the instruction of our Art Teacher, Mr. Palacio, our students have worked hard to paints portraits of dogs and cats currently sheltered at Animal Haven. His goal was to teach the children about human-animal bonding, as well as raise awareness about adoption.

Here is one of their kittens with her portraits, by Y. and S. from 3rd grade. Animal Haven will use these paintings to present to interested adopters, as well as hang them near the holding area. Head to your nearest shelter and get a friend for life <3.

Thank you for the opportunity! Our students had great fun creating these.

shared_text:
Manhattan Charter School
March 2017 ·

Apply to Manhattan Charter Schools for your children's next great education! https://goo.gl/8Xw3of

#whymcs Day 1 - Location location location.

Our 2 schools are located in the Lower East Side, with convenient public transportation (F, M, J, Z, and numerous bus services) and gateway to Brooklyn. This is a historical, culturally diverse and vibrant community, with whom we have developed a close relationship. Here's a picture of our 2nd grade hanging out with the firefighters of Engine 15 in LES. We learned a lot about fire safety and the profession that day, and even gained some future courageous firefighters!

#charterschool #nyccharterschool #manhattancharterschool #elementaryschool #publicschool #courage

At MCS, we believe teaching curiosity and critical thinking skills empowers children to be lifelong innovators and problem-solvers. Many of our students, like Janell, has gone on to achieve great things!
